.TH "WEBGL_lose_context" "JS" "July 26, 2024" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
WEBGL_lose_context \- WEBGL_lose_context extension
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]WEBGL_lose_context\f[R] extension is part of the WebGL API and
exposes functions to simulate losing and restoring a
\f[CR]WebGLRenderingContext\f[R].
.PP
WebGL extensions are available using the
\f[CR]WebGLRenderingContext.getExtension()\f[R] method.
For more information, see also Using Extensions in the WebGL tutorial.
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This extension is available to both, WebGL1 and WebGL2
contexts.
.RE
.SH INSTANCE METHODS
.TP
\f[B]WEBGL_lose_context.loseContext()\f[R]
Simulates losing the context.
.TP
\f[B]WEBGL_lose_context.restoreContext()\f[R]
Simulates restoring the context.
.SH EXAMPLES
With this extension, you can simulate the \f[CR]webglcontextlost\f[R]
and \f[CR]webglcontextrestored\f[R] events:
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] canvas = document.getElementById(\[dq]canvas\[dq]);
\f[B]const\f[R] gl = canvas.getContext(\[dq]webgl\[dq]);

canvas.addEventListener(\[dq]webglcontextlost\[dq], (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  console.log(event);
});

gl.getExtension(\[dq]WEBGL_lose_context\[dq]).loseContext();

\f[I]// WebGLContextEvent event with type \[dq]webglcontextlost\[dq] is logged.\f[R]
.EE
